'''Samantha Jane Barks''' (born 2 October 1990) is a [[Manx people|Manx]] actress and singer who rose to fame after placing third in the [[BBC]] [[talent show]]-themed television series ''[[I'd Do Anything (BBC TV series)|I'd Do Anything]]'' in 2008.<ref name="BBC-NANCYSSAMANTHA">{{cite news|title=Nancy Contestants&nbsp;– Samantha|publisher=BBC|date=22 March 2008|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/oliver/contestants/nancy/samantha.shtml |access-date=10 May 2008}}</ref> She has released three [[Album|studio albums]]: ''Looking in Your Eyes'' (2007), ''Samantha Barks'' (2016), and ''Into the Unknown'' (2021).

Barks made her film debut as [[Éponine]] in the [[Tom Hooper]]-directed ''[[Les Misérables (2012 film)|Les Misérables]]'' in 2012.<ref name="r1" /> Her performance in the film won her the [[Empire Award for Best Newcomer|Empire Award for Best Female Newcomer]] and a shared [[National Board of Review Award for Best Cast|National Board of Review Award]] with the film's cast.<ref>{{cite web |title=Awards of Samantha Barks |url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm2885819/awards |access-date=26 May 2013 |website=[[IMDb]]}}</ref> She starred opposite [[Jonathan Bailey]] in the [[Disney Channel]] musical-comedy ''[[Groove High]]'' (2012–2013) and again, in the London revival of the musical ''[[The Last Five Years]]'' in 2016.<ref name="blogspot1">{{Cite news |date=29 October 2012 |title=Disney Channel UK To Premiere New Series "Groove High" November 2012 |work=DisneyChannelEars |url=http://disneychannelears.blogspot.com/2012/10/disney-channel-uk-to-premiere-new.html |access-date=8 December 2012}}</ref> In 2018, she originated the role of Vivian Ward in ''[[Pretty Woman: The Musical]]'' on Broadway. From 2021 to 2024, she has starred as [[Elsa (Frozen)|Elsa]] in the [[West End theatre|West End]] production of ''[[Frozen (musical)|Frozen]].''<ref>{{Cite news |last=Wiegand |first=Chris |last2= |first2= |date=2024-09-09 |title=Letting it go: Frozen fans bid farewell to West End musical |url=https://www.theguardian.com/stage/article/2024/sep/09/frozen-fans-bid-farewell-to-west-end-musical-samantha-barks |access-date=2025-02-08 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> In 2025, Barks won the [[The Masked Singer (British TV series) series 6|sixth series]] of ''[[The Masked Singer (British TV series)|The Masked Singer]]''.<ref name="tms">{{Cite web |date=2025-02-15 |title=The Masked Singer UK crowns 2025 winner |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/tv/reality-tv/a63806290/masked-singer-uk-2025-winner/ |access-date=2025-02-15 |website=Digital Spy |language=en-GB}}</ref>

==Early life==
Barks was born and raised in [[Laxey]]<ref name="imot4095167">{{cite news|title=Super Sam Barks' star is rising|publisher=[[Isle of Man Newspapers]]|date=19 May 2008|url=http://www.iomtoday.co.im/news/Super-Sam-Barks-star-is.4095167.jp|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130108053708/http://www.iomtoday.co.im/news/Super-Sam-Barks-star-is.4095167.jp|url-status=dead|archive-date=8 January 2013|access-date=22 May 2008}}</ref> on the [[Isle of Man]]. Her mother is from [[Malahide]], Ireland.<ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://independent.ie/lifestyle/i-beat-taylor-to-star-in-les-mis-28957241.html|title=I beat Taylor to star in 'Les Mis'!|journal=The Irish Independent|first=Deirdre|last=Reynolds|date=10 January 2013|accessdate=21 February 2023}}</ref> Barks attended Laxey Primary School and [[St Ninian's High School, Douglas]].<ref name="SNHS65">{{cite news|title=Sam Barks update|publisher=St. Ninian's High School|date=30 April 2008|url=http://www.sch.im/snhs/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=65&Itemid=1|access-date=21 May 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080603145912/http://www.sch.im/snhs/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=65&Itemid=1|archive-date=3 June 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref>

